Sri Lanka beat Bangladesh by 75 runs in the second and final T20 International at Sylhet a short while ago.Batting first, Sri Lanka made 210 for 4 and in reply, the home team was bowled out for 135 in 18.4 overs.Bangladesh skipper Mahmudulla was the top scorer for the home team with 41 off 31 balls.Tamim Iqbal made 29.Shehan Madushanka who suffered a leg injury while bowling his third over picked up 2 for 23.Dhanushka Gunathilaka also bagged 2 wickets.With this win, Sri Lanka recorded a 2 nil victory in the 2-match series.